*"anarchos semitas"* it's the idea that, physically and  philosophically, we go to discovery, to vagrancy, to encounters.
It's also the idea that we do not follow the too-easily-established roads and thoughts.
Indeed, we have a profound need to build our lives without bias neither strict goal,
along ambulatory paths, along *"anarchic paths"*.

## The beginning of a long travel

Throughout our lives, we would like to do a lot of travels, small or large (in distance, duration or hardness).
We would like to be there as children (naive and cheerful) and always think to be at the beginning.
Therefore, our lives would be *the beginning of a long travel*.
